This paper discusses the automatic analysis of sentiment and position-taking in parliamentary debates, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which focuses on natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other likely sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval), as these fields also involve machine learning and data analysis techniques that could be applied to the problem of sentiment and position-taking analysis.
